  "metadata": {
    "what_it_measures": "Foreign holdings of US Treasury securities (billions). Reported monthly by the Treasury International Capital (TIC) system. Includes central banks, sovereign wealth funds, and foreign investors.\n",
    "why_it_matters": "Measures foreign demand for US Treasuries. Declining foreign holdings can signal reduced confidence in US fiscal trajectory, pushing yields higher. 12-month change direction is the key signal.\n",
